column1: 11/18/2012,Taking too much contraceptives may harm your health. It may cause abdominal and chest pain nausea weight gain headache etc.
11/19/2012,If someone infected with HIV does not take proper treatment then it usually takes around ten years for AIDS to develop.
11/20/2012,Dark chocolates contain anti-oxidants and phenylethylamine which evoke feeling of being in love. They also prevent against infections.
11/21/2012,The missionary position is the best one for conception. This position enables the sperm to reach the closest to the vagina.
11/22/2012,Unsafe oral sex is as risky as intercourse. Forced oral sex can lead to injuries both in the mouth and genitals and pain during urination.
11/23/2012,If a pregnant woman is infected with HIV she can transmit the virus to her baby during pregnancy labour and delivery or breastfeeding.
11/24/2012,An HIV positive woman and an HIV negative man can conceive without HIV transmission occurring by using artificial insemination.
11/25/2012,It is widely prevalent fact that sex leads to an increase in the energy levels. It reduces stress and results in weight loss.
11/26/2012,Oral sex does not carry the threat of unwanted pregnancy as the semen is ejected in the mouth or on the body. You can't conceive through it.
11/27/2012,Condoms are the most effective contraceptive methods to prevent contracting HIV-infection. They are better than birth control pills.
11/28/2012,Taking Vitamin B-Complex i.e Vitamin B1 to B5 and B-12 help to raise your sexual desire. They improve the blood circulation as well.
11/29/2012,Practicing oral sex with more than one partner might lead to the transmission of STDs i.e Sexually Transmitted Diseases.
11/30/2012,Lying side by side during the penetration would put lesser strain on both the partners. It is helpful for women who are overweight.
12/1/2012,Just closing your eyes and kissing your partner is stimulus enough to get a desired response of being up intimate and one.
12/2/2012,According to sex therapists women who have had amazing sex are the ones who feel good about their body. So love yourself first.
